name: Uluru - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
This muted redwood colored nail polish is inspired by and named after the large sandstone rock formation found in Australia. Uluru, or Ayers Rock, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is sacred to the aboriginal people of the area. The monolith has rich indigenous history and myths and legends surrounding it that go back thousands of years. The area around the formation has ancient paintings, rock caves, springs and waterholes and is known to give off a reddish pink hue in the sunlight.

Uluru is a muted redwood nail polish with cool brown undertones. Uluru is more brown and less saturated than Cusco.

name: Rotomahana - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Rotomahana's iridescent light white-pink color is named after Lake Rotomahana in New Zealand, and inspired by the pink and white terraces, also known as Te Otukapuarangi - Maori for the fountain of the clouded sky. This natural wonder was once considered the largest silica sinter deposit in the world and was sometimes referred to as the 8th wonder of the world in the 1800s. In 1886, Mount Tarawera erupted and the terraces were thought to have been destroyed.

Rotomahana is an almost-iridescent light pink breathable nail polish.

description:
786 Cosmetics presents a new soy polish remover with new ingredients!

Our 4 oz Soy-Based Nail Polish Remover is designed to gently remove nail polish. Jojoba Seed Oil replenishes the health and moisturization of your nails that was lost due to acetone-based nail polish removers.

Tea Tree Oil helps to counter cracked and damaged cuticles.

This product does not contain acetone or harsh acetates which will damage your nails, cuticles, and dry out your skin.

4 fl. oz / 118 mL

--

Directions for use:
Saturate a cotton ball or cotton pad with the Soy-Based Nail Polish Remover. Wipe all nails and allow the remover to absorb into the nail for at least 20-30 seconds. Wipe each nail until the polish is fully removed. Wash hands and nails thoroughly and dry well. Make sure the nail bed is dry and clean before applying new nail polish.

name: Nail Rescue Primer
description:
Our Nail Rescue Primer is the perfect start to any manicure! The Nail Rescue Primer works to strengthen weak and damaged nails and repair them for strong, healthy nails.

--

Directions for use:

Step 1: Apply two coats of 786 Cosmetics' Nail Rescue Primer and leave to dry. Make sure to dry fully between coats.

Step 2: Once dried, leave on for 5-7 days to allow for the Nail Rescue Primer to work to strengthen and repair the nails.

Step 3: Remove the Nail Rescue Primer with our Soy-Based Nail Polish Remover and enjoy your stronger nails!

**Nail Rescue Primer can also be applied as a base coat under your favorite nail polish! The primer is not water permeable so is it not recommended to use as a base coat if you are praying.

name: Baghdad - Breathable Nail Polish
description: This nude color was inspired by the sandy capital of Iraq, Baghdad [buhg-dad]. Once known as the world’s “centre of learning” and the largest city of the Middle Ages, the city was significantly destroyed by the Mongols in the 13th century and then again by the 2003 Invasion of Iraq. Though many of the cultural and historical pieces of the city are gone, there are still some that stand today, like the Al-Khulafa Mosque. This 10th century mosque dates back to the abbasid era and its sand-toned architecture is the main inspiration for the color.

name: Sakura - Breathable Nail Polish
description:
Sakura [saa-kur-uh] is inspired by the stunning pale pink cherry blossoms found in Sakura, Japan. In fact, the most common of all the cherry blossoms are called "Sakura" or Japanese Cherry. Located in Chiba prefecture, Sakura has been inhabited since prehistory and is home to the National Museum of Japanese History. Sakura blossoms are seen as a symbol of renewal, rebirth and new beginnings. Sakura blossoms only bloom for a brief time - best viewed during Spring time in Japan.

Sakura is best described as a muted pink nude, nearly opaque with two coats.

name: Soy Nail Polish Remover With Almond Essential Oil

breadcrumbs.name: Soy Nail Polish Remover With Almond Essential Oil

description:
Our 4 oz Soy-Based Nail Polish Remover is designed to gently remove nail polish. Almond Essential Oil promotes healthy, moisturized nails.

This product does not contain acetone or harsh acetates which will damage your nails and cuticles, and dry out your skin.

4 fl. oz / 118 mL

--

Directions for use:
Saturate a cotton ball or cotton pad with the Soy-Based Nail Polish Remover. Wipe all nails and allow the remover to absorb into the nail for at least 20-30 seconds. Wipe each nail until the polish is fully removed. Wash hands and nails thoroughly and dry well. Make sure the nail bed is dry and clean before applying polish.

name: Almond & Ginseng Cuticle Oil
description:
Our softening cuticle oil is enhanced with a blend of natural almond and ginseng oils which work to moisturize your cuticles and improve the look of your nails. This cuticle oil protects the cuticle and nail against damage to enhance the health and appearance of the nail and is the perfect first step to your manicure!

Directions for use:

Step 1: Apply a small drop of the Almond and Ginseng Cuticle Oil on your bare nails near the cuticle.

Step 2: Massage the cuticle oil into the nail to moisturize and soften the cuticle and promote nail growth.
Step 3: Once the nail and cuticle are softened, wash hands with soap and water. Once dry, apply your favorite 786 Cosmetics nail polish and enjoy your beautiful nails!
